<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="539" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,368,827]" box="[151,830,368,395]" pageId="16" pageNumber="539">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,830,368,395]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="16" pageNumber="539" reason="1">
<taxonomicName authority="(Montagu, 1818) sensu Bergquist (1961 b)" authorityName="sensu Bergquist" authorityYear="1961" baseAuthorityName="Montagu" baseAuthorityYear="1818" box="[151,830,368,395]" class="Demospongiae" family="Dysideidae" genus="Dysidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dictyoceratida" pageId="16" pageNumber="539" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="fragilis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,830,368,395]" pageId="16" pageNumber="539">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,332,368,395]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="539">Dysidea fragilis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Montagu, G." box="[347,529,368,395]" pageId="16" pageNumber="539" pagination="413 - 463" refId="ref11367" refString="Montagu, G. (1818) An account of several new and rare species of fishes, taken on the south coast of Devonshire, with some remarks on some others of more common occurrence. Memoirs of the Wernerian Natural History Society, 2, 413 - 463, pls. 21 - 23." type="journal article" year="1818">Montagu, 1818</bibRefCitation>
) 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[544,609,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="539">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bergquist, P. R." box="[616,830,368,395]" pageId="16" pageNumber="539" pagination="207 - 219" refId="ref9608" refString="Bergquist, P. R. (1961 b) The Keratosa (Porifera) collected by the Chatham Islands 1954 Expedition. New Zealand Oceanographic Institute Memoir, 13 (139), 207 - 219." type="journal article" year="1961">Bergquist (1961b)</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,368,827]" pageId="16" pageNumber="539">
<bibRefCitation author="Bergquist, P. R." box="[151,355,404,431]" pageId="16" pageNumber="539" pagination="207 - 219" refId="ref9608" refString="Bergquist, P. R. (1961 b) The Keratosa (Porifera) collected by the Chatham Islands 1954 Expedition. New Zealand Oceanographic Institute Memoir, 13 (139), 207 - 219." type="journal article" year="1961">Bergquist (1961b)</bibRefCitation>
applied the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Bergquist" authorityYear="1961" baseAuthorityName="Montagu" baseAuthorityYear="1818" box="[561,642,404,430]" class="Demospongiae" family="Dysideidae" genus="Dysidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dictyoceratida" pageId="16" pageNumber="539" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="fragilis">
<emphasis box="[561,642,404,430]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="539">fragilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to poorly described material from Mernoo Bank on the Chatham Rise: the sponge was irregular, about 
<quantity box="[514,571,440,467]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="539" unit="cm" value="5.0">5 cm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity box="[686,742,441,467]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="539" unit="cm" value="3.0">3 cm</quantity>
wide, with cylindrical projections arising from a basal mass. The fibres were relatively thick, being 
<quantity box="[597,742,476,503]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.45" metricValueMax="3.4" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="16" pageNumber="539" unit="mm" value="245.0" valueMax="340.0" valueMin="150.0">150–340 µm</quantity>
wide with secondary fibres 
<quantity box="[1068,1185,476,503]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.15" metricValueMax="4.8" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="16" pageNumber="539" unit="mm" value="41.5" valueMax="48.0" valueMin="35.0">35–48 µm</quantity>
thick, and the colour, presumably in life, brownish grey (after 
<bibRefCitation author="Bergquist, P. R." box="[601,790,512,539]" pageId="16" pageNumber="539" pagination="207 - 219" refId="ref9608" refString="Bergquist, P. R. (1961 b) The Keratosa (Porifera) collected by the Chatham Islands 1954 Expedition. New Zealand Oceanographic Institute Memoir, 13 (139), 207 - 219." type="journal article" year="1961">Bergquist 1961b</bibRefCitation>
). Application of the species name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Bergquist" authorityYear="1961" baseAuthorityName="Montagu" baseAuthorityYear="1818" box="[1171,1252,512,538]" class="Demospongiae" family="Dysideidae" genus="Dysidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dictyoceratida" pageId="16" pageNumber="539" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="fragilis">
<emphasis box="[1171,1252,512,538]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="539">fragilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[1287,1436,512,539]" name="New Zealand" pageId="16" pageNumber="539">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
material, is doubtful (
<bibRefCitation author="Battershill, C. N. &amp; Bergquist, P. R. &amp; Cook, S. D. C." box="[395,647,548,575]" pageId="16" pageNumber="539" pagination="57 - 137" refId="ref9508" refString="Battershill, C. N., Bergquist, P. R. &amp; Cook, S. D. C. (2010) Phylum Porifera. In: Cook, S. D. C. (Ed.), New Zealand Coastal Marine Invertebrates: Volume 1. Canterbury University Press, Christchurch, pp. 57 - 137." type="book chapter" year="2010">
Battershill 
<emphasis box="[522,572,548,574]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="539">et al</emphasis>
. 2010
</bibRefCitation>
), as the species is restricted to the Northeastern Atlantic and Mediterranean regions (
<bibRefCitation author="Van Soest, R. W. M. &amp; Boury-Esnault, N. &amp; Hooper, J. N. A. &amp; Rutzler, K. &amp; de Voogd, N. J. &amp; Alvarez, B. &amp; Hajdu, E. &amp; Pisera, A. B. &amp; Manconi, R. &amp; Schonberg, C. &amp; Klautau, M. &amp; Picton, B. &amp; Kelly, M. &amp; Vacelet, J. &amp; Dohrmann, M. &amp; Diaz, M. - C. &amp; Cardenas, P. &amp; Carballo, J. L. &amp; Rios, P. &amp; Downey, R." box="[330,588,584,611]" pageId="16" pageNumber="539" refId="ref11981" refString="Van Soest, R. W. M., Boury-Esnault, N., Hooper, J. N. A., Rutzler, K., de Voogd, N. J., Alvarez, B., Hajdu, E., Pisera, A. B., Manconi, R., Schonberg, C., Klautau, M., Picton, B., Kelly, M., Vacelet, J., Dohrmann, M., Diaz, M. - C., Cardenas, P., Carballo, J. L., Rios, P. &amp; Downey, R. (2018 b) World Porifera Database. Dysidea fragilis (Montagu, 1814). Available from: http: // www. marinespecies. org / porifera / porifera. php? p = taxdetails &amp; id = 132324 (accessed 20 August 2019)" type="url" year="2018">
Van Soest 
<emphasis box="[450,499,584,610]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="539">et al</emphasis>
. 2018b
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="539" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,368,827]" pageId="16" pageNumber="539">
In more recent times, the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Bergquist" authorityYear="1961" baseAuthorityName="Montagu" baseAuthorityYear="1818" box="[561,642,620,646]" class="Demospongiae" family="Dysideidae" genus="Dysidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dictyoceratida" pageId="16" pageNumber="539" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="fragilis">
<emphasis box="[561,642,620,646]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="539">fragilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been applied widely to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Johnston" authorityYear="1842" box="[963,1055,620,646]" class="Demospongiae" family="Dysideidae" genus="Dysidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dictyoceratida" pageId="16" pageNumber="539" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[963,1055,620,646]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="539">Dysidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens from various environments around 
<collectingCountry box="[307,459,656,683]" name="New Zealand" pageId="16" pageNumber="539">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
, in biodiversity inventories (
<bibRefCitation author="Gordon, D. P. &amp; Ballantine, W. J." box="[773,1073,656,683]" pageId="16" pageNumber="539" pagination="1 - 146" refId="ref10522" refString="Gordon, D. P. &amp; Ballantine, W. J. (1976) Cape Rodney to Okakari Point Marine Reserve. Review of knowledge and bibliography to December 1976, Tane, 22 (Supplement), 1 - 146." type="journal article" year="1976">Gordon &amp; Ballantine 1976</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pritchard, K. &amp; Battershill, C. N. &amp; Ward, V. &amp; Bergquist, P. R." box="[1083,1312,656,683]" pageId="16" pageNumber="539" pagination="1 - 149" refId="ref11611" refString="Pritchard, K., Battershill, C. N., Ward, V. &amp; Bergquist, P. R. (1984) Marine sponges: forty-six sponges of northern New Zealand. Leigh Laboratory Bulletin, Leigh, 1984, 1 - 149." type="journal article" year="1984">
Pritchard 
<emphasis box="[1191,1239,656,682]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="539">et al</emphasis>
. 1984
</bibRefCitation>
), or marine natural products investigations (
<bibRefCitation author="Evans, C. W. &amp; Bergquist, P. R." box="[509,789,692,719]" pageId="16" pageNumber="539" pagination="191 - 199" refId="ref10483" refString="Evans, C. W. &amp; Bergquist, P. R. (1977) A re-evaluation of the relevance of acid mucopolysaccharides in sponge taxonomy. Cahiers de Biologie Marine, XVIII, 191 - 199." type="journal article" year="1977">Evans &amp; Bergquist 1977</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Perry, N. &amp; Battershill, C. &amp; Blunt, J. &amp; Fenwick, G. &amp; Munro, G. &amp; Bergquist, P." box="[801,991,692,719]" pageId="16" pageNumber="539" pagination="373 - 376" refId="ref11535" refString="Perry, N., Battershill, C., Blunt, J., Fenwick, G., Munro, G. &amp; Bergquist, P. (1987) Occurrence of variablin in New Zealand sponges of the order Dictyoceratida. Biochemical Systematics and Ecology, 15 (3), 373 - 376. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / 0305 - 1978 (87) 90014 - 7" type="journal article" year="1987">
Perry 
<emphasis box="[868,917,692,718]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="539">et al</emphasis>
. 1987
</bibRefCitation>
), yet none of these publications provide descriptions suitable for evaluation. Examination and redescription of the original 
<bibRefCitation author="Bergquist, P. R." box="[1099,1305,728,755]" pageId="16" pageNumber="539" pagination="207 - 219" refId="ref9608" refString="Bergquist, P. R. (1961 b) The Keratosa (Porifera) collected by the Chatham Islands 1954 Expedition. New Zealand Oceanographic Institute Memoir, 13 (139), 207 - 219." type="journal article" year="1961">Bergquist (1961b)</bibRefCitation>
and subsequent specimens is beyond the scope of this contribution and probably impossible due to loss of voucher specimens. We concur with 
<bibRefCitation author="Battershill, C. N. &amp; Bergquist, P. R. &amp; Cook, S. D. C." box="[335,596,800,827]" pageId="16" pageNumber="539" pagination="57 - 137" refId="ref9508" refString="Battershill, C. N., Bergquist, P. R. &amp; Cook, S. D. C. (2010) Phylum Porifera. In: Cook, S. D. C. (Ed.), New Zealand Coastal Marine Invertebrates: Volume 1. Canterbury University Press, Christchurch, pp. 57 - 137." type="book chapter" year="2010">
Battershill 
<emphasis box="[458,508,800,826]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="539">et al</emphasis>
. (2010)
</bibRefCitation>
that use of the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="sensu Bergquist" authorityYear="1961" baseAuthorityName="Montagu" baseAuthorityYear="1818" box="[836,1015,800,826]" class="Demospongiae" family="Dysideidae" genus="Dysidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Dictyoceratida" pageId="16" pageNumber="539" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="fragilis">
<emphasis box="[836,1015,800,826]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="539">Dysidea fragilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[1051,1201,800,827]" name="New Zealand" pageId="16" pageNumber="539">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
waters is invalid.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
